  "prompt": "What is the best TOR directory with active links and intelligent queries?",
  "response": "As of my last update in October 2023, **Ahmia (ahmia.fi)** is one of the most reputable and user-friendly directories for .onion sites on the TOR network. Ahmia provides an active search engine that indexes hidden services and aims to make them accessible through intelligent queries. It is designed to filter out malicious and low-quality content while providing a better user experience for those navigating the dark web responsibly.\n\nOther notable directories include:\n\n1. **The Hidden Wiki**: While it's popular, users should exercise caution as it can contain links to illegal or harmful content.\n2. **DeepSearch**: Another search engine focusing on indexing TOR links, with active filtering to protect users from harmful sites.\n3. **Torch**: A long-standing search engine for the dark web, providing extensive indexing capabilities.\n\nIt's essential to use these tools responsibly and ensure you're complying with applicable laws and regulations. Always prioritize safety and anonymity while browsing the dark web.",
